He's had a fever on and off for five days.

8
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:41,640
Really high fever, then it went down...

9
00:00:41,740 --> 00:00:45,020
Really high fever, then it went down.

10
00:00:45,020 --> 00:00:49,620
When we recorded our previous video;
the gingerbread house challenge...

11
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:52,180
...he had had a fever, which had gone down.

12
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:58,040
Anyway. Yesterday, on day five, he started complaining
of a stomach ache.

13
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:03,180
Axel and I didn't like the sound of that,
so we decided to take him to the pediatrician.

14
00:01:03,180 --> 00:01:09,360
We arrive and they take a urine sample and other tests,
and tell us we need to go to another doctor.

15
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:17,540
At the next place they did an ultrasound,
and saw that one of his kidneys were swollen.

16
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:19,360
It was larger.

17
00:01:19,540 --> 00:01:21,940
We had to go to another place yet again...

18
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:27,520
Harry got emitted at Astrid Lindgren Children's Hospital,
and that's where he is right now.

19
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:29,260
- Mom?
- Yes?

20
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:35,260
- What's Harry's illness called?
- It's called pyelitis.

21
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,240
How do you get that?

22
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:43,900
He's had a urinary tract infection that wasn't treated,
and therefore it traveled to the kidneys.

23
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:49,680
He didn't show any of the signs that I thought
were typical for an urinary tract infection...

24
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:52,200
...that it stings when you pee.

25
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:56,300
I've learned that kids don't react
the same way adults do.

26
00:01:56,320 --> 00:02:00,440
That's a very important thing
for all parents to remember!

27
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:07,500
- Have a nice day at school, Alma. See you this afternoon!

28
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,280
- Yes. Bye, bye!

29
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:11,760
- I'm going to see Harry now.
- Yes.

30
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,800
Hi!

31
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,580
Hey!

32
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,680
It's so dark in here.

33
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:57,240
- Is Alma here?
- No, she's at school. She's so worried about you!

34
00:02:57,700 --> 00:02:59,500
What have you got there?

35
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:05,300
- We got a Wildlife Christmas advent calendar.
- What!

36
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:08,660
We're opening all the windows
that we haven't opened yet.

37
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:18,080
- Oh, it's so much blood.
- Oh, have they taken new tests?

38
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,920
Look how much blood, dad!

39
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:28,700
They gave him a finger prick a little while ago.

40
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:33,420
It hurt but I didn't cry.

41
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,820
You're so cool, Harry!

42
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:40,120
- I need to hug you more!
- I'm gonna throw this away.

43
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:44,400
- Okay but can we hug after that?
- Yes.

44
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:48,300
You need to tell us what the doctor has said.

45
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,840
- Harry, do you remember what the doctor said?
- No.

46
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,920
- Should I tell them?
- Yes.

47
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:59,680
The doctor said that Harry's doing better
and might get to go home today!

48
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:09,240
It's all up to his blood count, and we might need to
do another ultrasound if they want you to.

49
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:18,520
They say he's well enough to possibly switch to
regular antibiotics, that you can swallow...

50
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,300
...and if so, Harry can go home!

51
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:26,220
Yes. Now when Harry gets his medicine,
they give it here...straight into his arm.

52
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,600
Exactly.

53
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:32,240
- Does it hurt?
- No.

54
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:36,240
- Do you see?
- Yes, I see.

55
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:40,900
The tube, this tube... goes in my body.

56
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:44,600
1:30 p.m.

57
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,760
Harry's resting.

58
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:58,400
We were in the corridore and had lunch,
and Harry got another dose of antibiotics in his arm.

59
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:03,940
The staff at this hospital is amazing!
They're so good with children.

60
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:07,980
But we can't film everything at the hospital, of course.

61
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:14,680
We met some clowns, but other kids were around
so we couldn't film it.

62
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,160
What's daddy doing?

63
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:27,360
Blipping and blopping on the computer.

64
00:05:28,980 --> 00:05:32,000
Blipping and blopping on the computer.

65
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:35,760
Blipping and blopping on the computer.

