107
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,920
There.

108
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:53,540
It's almost 5:30 p.m.

109
00:08:55,060 --> 00:08:58,740
This means it's time to pee again.

110
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:12,140
Okay...

111
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:16,240
There!

112
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:20,900
Then the pee one...

113
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,800
- On here?
- Mhm!

114
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:29,480
I peed on the poop.

115
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:37,840
The doctors were just in here and said that
Harry need to stay here one more night.

116
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:47,140
The bacteria that caused the UTI that then
traveled to the kidneys, is a rare kind.

117
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,400
They don't feel safe letting him go home.

118
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:55,340
Hi.

119
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,560
Hey.

120
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:05,040
Hi, dear...

121
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:07,780
Oh, you're not feeling well at all...

122
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:09,860
This is for you.

123
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:16,420
He's all groggy...

124
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:24,100
Yes, he got really sleepy when he got
this drip with medicine.

125
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,220
Oh...

126
00:10:29,140 --> 00:10:30,740
(One hour later)

127
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:33,340
Alma, look down!

128
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,340
Pretty high up...

129
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,520
Hey hey, kids!

130
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,760
This is as high as we can go.

131
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:49,920
- What are you two doing?
- Eating french fries and riding the elevator!

132
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:04,260
♪ Oopsie woopsie, the tush is falling off! ♪
(funny changes to a Christmas song)

133
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:10,680
♪ When the tush is here every tush shall be happy! ♪

134
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:16,480
We've never been this happy that
the kids sing about pee and poop!

135
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,200
I also want to lay down.

136
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:22,820
He seemed very unwell for a while there.
But now the energy's coming back.

137
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:30,360
Alma and Joanna are leaving now
to go home and sleep.

138
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:33,080
Harry and I will get ready for bed.

139
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:37,060
We've ordered a taxi. It's already 9 p.m.

140
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,920
- I'm really tired.
- Me too!

141
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:46,140
We won't film anymore today.
We'll resume tomorrow, Harry.

142
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,460
- Mhm.
- Mhm.

143
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:50,280
Okay, let's say goodnight...

144
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:54,460
No, I mean: see you soon! Then it's a new day.

145
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:16,140
What are you holding?

146
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:18,240
A balloon sword.

147
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,160
Where did you get it from?

148
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,980
Clowns.

149
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:28,040
- There's been clowns here?
- Yes.

150
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:32,840
He's feeling a lot better!

151
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:38,960
His body has responded to the treatment,
so his white blood cell count has gone down.

152
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:43,540
That means we might get to go home today! Yay!

153
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,520
I died.

154
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:58,020
What kind of clowns were here?

155
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:07,400
Fjodor and Milda Matilda knocked on the door,
