156
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:12,600
- Yes!
- They played with whoopee cushions, and tied balloons.

157
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:17,260
They were great. Very good for him!

158
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,680
Harry, does it hurt?

159
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,460
No.

160
00:13:31,260 --> 00:13:33,400
Now I'm removing it...

161
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:36,060
There! You did great!

162
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:41,920
How cool is Harry?!

163
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:49,240
You didn't even flinch when they were sticking you with needles, and removing needles, and such!

164
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:54,300
- I think he's totally awesome!
- Like a superhero!

165
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:58,640
Yes, way cooler than your mom! I'm like...

166
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:03,000
I'm holding the camera and feeling a tear fall.

167
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,780
Let's be quiet.

168
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,380
- Harry, do you know what happens now?
- No?

169
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:13,020
We get to go home... We get to go home!

170
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,900
I'm getting a fart on my neck.

171
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,520
How cozy...

172
00:14:44,660 --> 00:14:47,620
We're back home again...

173
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,920
And it's so nice!

174
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:56,640
Don't you agree, Alma?

175
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:59,660
Yes, it's nice as can be!

176
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,940
It's so cozy!

177
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,240
We've got an important thing to do...

178
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:11,540
- Cut off the hospital wristband!
- Yes, which you get when you're in the hospital.

179
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:14,080
- Harry, are you ready?
- Yes.

180
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:16,620
Goodbye.

181
00:15:17,660 --> 00:15:20,080
How wonderful!

182
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:27,040
Group hug! Group hug! Group hug!

183
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,880
What an emotional roller coaster it's been...

184
00:15:30,940 --> 00:15:34,940
- I'm completely drained...
- Me too. Completely exhausted.

185
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:37,100
- And grateful!
- Yes!

186
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:41,280
- That Harry's home!
- Yes, it's so nice that he's getting better.

187
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,660
I have so much respect for parents
with children that are sick.

188
00:15:45,660 --> 00:15:46,800
Yes!

189
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:51,600
After our brief hospital stay I'm thinking;
God, some go through this...

190
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:52,800
Mhm...

191
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,860
